From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrey Kasaurov <andrey.kasaurov@amd.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2099 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] hipBLASLt TensileLite: disable real-true16 for GFX11+
 assembler invocations

hipBLASLt ships its own internal copy of TensileLite under
projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/ that is separate from the shared
TensileLite in shared/tensile/.  The shared copy was already patched
(patch 0001) but the hipBLASLt-internal copy still lacked the
-Wa,-mattr=-real-true16 flag, causing identical assembler failures
when building hipBLASLt kernels for GFX11+ targets on the amd-main
compiler branch.

Pass -Wa,-mattr=-real-true16 in the Assembler component for GFX11+
so the assembler accepts the legacy operand syntax.  The -Wa, prefix
is required because clang++ does not accept bare -mattr as a driver
flag; the prefix forwards it to the integrated assembler backend.
---
 projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Component.py | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Component.py b/projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Component.py
index 67fa35e2d8..5924d00aa4 100644
--- a/projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Component.py
+++ b/projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Component.py
@@ -169,10 +169,13 @@ class Assembler(Component):
             destPath: The destination path for the generated object file.
         """
         args = self._default_args
+        gfx_major = int(targetGfx.replace("gfx", "")[:2]) if targetGfx.startswith("gfx") else 0
+        mattr_args = ["-Wa,-mattr=-real-true16"] if gfx_major >= 11 else []
         args = [
             *args,
             f"-mcpu={targetGfx}",
             "-mwavefrontsize64" if wavefrontSize == 64 else "-mno-wavefrontsize64",
+            *mattr_args,
             srcPath,
             "-o",
             destPath
